description: This attractive West Sussex village is located just to the west of Billingshurst on the edge of the South Downs National Park. This circular walk from the village visits The Mens Nature Reserve and the River Wey. The reserve is located just to the south west of Wisborough Green and includes some woodland trails with lots of wildlife to see. You can then link up with the Wey South Path and enjoy some nice views of the River Arun. To continue your walking in the area head east to pick up the Billingshurst Canal and River Walk where you can enjoy further walks along the popular Wey South Path. Please scroll down for the full list of walks near and around Wisborough Green. The detailed maps below also show a range of footpaths, bridleways and cycle paths in the area.

details.subtitle: Pubs/Cafes
details.content: The Three Crowns is a fine village pub located in the heart of Wisborough Green adjacent to the quintessential cricket green. They serve good food and have a lovely garden area. The pub is dog friendly and can be found at postcode RH14 0DX.
